FBIS4-55424 "dreeu094_k_94003" FBIS-EEU-94-094 Daily Report 14 May 1994 CROATIA U.S. Asked To Support UNPA Reintegration U.S. Asked To Support UNPA Reintegration LD1405185394 Zagreb HTV Television in Serbo-Croatian 1730 GMT 14 May 94 LD1405185394 Zagreb HTV Television Serbo-Croatian BFN [Excerpt] In Geneva, Croatia has submitted a request to the United States to lend its support in speeding up the process of the reintegration of UN Protected Areas [UNPA's] into Croatia. During a meeting with US Secretary of State Warren Christopher, Minister Granic asked the U.S. Government to lend its firm support in the case of Croatia's borders. The meeting took place in the UN embassy in Geneva before the formal ceremony held to mark the Croat-Muslim agreement. Ministers Granic and Christopher talked about the situation in the UNPA and about bilateral relations. After a cooperation agreement was reached they stressed a need for more specific agreements between Croatia and the United States in the future. [Begin Granic recording] One of the important topics was U.S. support to the Republic of Croatia regarding an approach to the international financial institutions, more specifically, the credits of the World Bank [word indistinct] the European Bank for Reconstruction and Development. [passage omitted]
